Senate Resolution 50
By: Senators Sims of the 12th, Davenport of the 17th, Jackson of the 41st, Halpern of the
39th, Jones II of the 22nd and others
A RESOLUTION
1 Commending the Georgia Youth Science & Technology Centers (GYSTC) as well as the
2 2025 Don Cargill STEM Scholars for their innovative and integrated teaching of science,
3 technology, engineering, and mathematics in kindergarten through eighth grade classrooms;
4 and for other purposes.
5 WHEREAS, GYSTC is headquartered at Kennesaw State University with ten additional
6 program sites across the state; and
7 WHEREAS, GYSTC was founded in April 1989 to promote interest and enthusiasm in
8 STEM; and
9 WHEREAS, GYSTC works to improve the teaching and learning process by enhancing
10 teaching methods and content knowledge; and
11 WHEREAS, GYSTC encourages students to pursue STEM careers; and
12 WHEREAS, GYSTC works to provide a greater and better-qualified workforce for Georgia's
13 industries in the rural and underserved regions of the state; and
