14 WHEREAS, GYSTC's is committed to professional learning for and recognition of teachers'
15 innovative work to improve students' learning; and
16 WHEREAS, with better quality teachers and higher student achievement, GYSTC will help
17 to broaden the pipeline of science, technology, engineering, and mathematics majors for
18 Georgia's workforce.
19 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
20 commend the Georgia Youth Science & Technology Centers (GYSTC) for their work,
21 dedication, and devoted service to all teachers of Georgia and especially the 2025 Don
22 Cargill STEM Scholars who demonstrate innovation and hard work in their classrooms.
23 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
24 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the Georgia Youth
25 Science & Technology Centers.
